Office of Disciplinary Counsel v. Dubyak.

[Cite as Disciplinary Counsel v. Dubyak (2002), 94 Ohio St.3d 1214.]

(No. 00-2284 Submitted and decided January 10, 2002.)

This cause came on for further consideration upon the filing of an application for reinstatement by respondent, Joseph Dubyak, Attorney Registration No. 0025054, last known business address in Cleveland, Ohio.

The court coming now to consider its order of May 30, 2001, wherein the court, pursuant to Gov.Bar R. V(6)(B)(3), suspended respondent for a period of two years, with six months stayed and with credit for time served since May 31, 2000, finds that respondent has substantially complied with that order and with the provisions of Gov.Bar R. V(10)(A). Therefore,

IT IS ORDERED by this court that Joseph Dubyak be and hereby is reinstated to the practice of law in the state of Ohio.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that the Clerk of this court issue certified copies of this order as provided for in Gov.Bar R. V(8)(D)(1), that publication be made as provided for in Gov.Bar R. V(8)(D)(2), and that respondent bear the costs of publication.

For earlier cases, see In re Dubyak (2000), 89 Ohio St.3d 1419, 729 N.E.2d 389; and Disciplinary Counsel v. Dubyak (2001), 92 Ohio St.3d 18, 748 N.E.2d 26.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer, Cook and Lundberg Stratton, JJ., concur.
